    <text>
        <body>
            <p>TEI Customization for PUCC editions.</p>
            <!-- originally generated from 1.9.0 p5 -->
            <div>
                <head>Overall structure</head>
                <p>A PUCC edition is a single TEI document, represented using the following elements: <specList>
                        <specDesc key="TEI"/>
                        <specDesc key="text"/>
                        <specDesc key="teiHeader"/>
                        <specDesc key="facsimile"/>
                    </specList></p>
                <p>These elements must all be present, except for a <gi>facsimile</gi> which is needed only in the case
                    where a PUCC edition integrates page images in addition to transcribed text and commentary. </p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <head>Front, body, and back</head>
                <p> Each TEI <gi>text</gi> contains the edited transcription of a primary source, including any
                    annotation, introduction, commentary, indexes, etc. These components are organized using the
                    following elements: <specList>
                        <specDesc key="front"/>
                        <specDesc key="body"/>
                        <specDesc key="back"/>
                        <specDesc key="div"/>
                    </specList>A <gi>text</gi> element must have a <gi>body</gi> element, usually preceded by a
                        <gi>front</gi>, and optionally followed by a <gi>back</gi>. </p>
                <p>Each of these three components may may be subdivided hierarchically using the <gi>div</gi>
                    element.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <head>Front matter</head>
                <p>For early print books, it may be useful to capture the original prefatory matter within the
                        <gi>front</gi> element, using the following specialised elements, in addition to the generic
                        <gi>div</gi>
                    <specList>
                        <specDesc key="docAuthor"/>
                        <specDesc key="docDate"/>
                        <specDesc key="docEdition"/>
                        <specDesc key="docImprint"/>
                        <specDesc key="docTitle"/>
                        <specDesc key="epigraph"/>
                        <specDesc key="imprimatur"/>
                        <specDesc key="titlePage"/>
                        <specDesc key="titlePart"/>
                    </specList></p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <head>Divisions and their components</head>
                <p>The <gi>div</gi> element is used for any structural subdivision of a text, such as a chapter,
                    section, subsection etc. The <att>type</att> attribute is used to distinguish divisions with
                    different functions; its value should be taken from the following list: <specList>
                        <specDesc key="div" atts="type"/>
                    </specList>
                </p>
                <p>A division will typically begin with at least one heading, and may have several. The following
                    elements are from the divLiminal class are used to mark these: <specList>
                        <specDesc key="head"/>
                        <specDesc key="byline"/>
                        <specDesc key="dateline"/>
                        <specDesc key="opener"/>
                        <specDesc key="closer"/>
                        <specDesc key="signed"/>
                        <specDesc key="salute"/>
                    </specList></p>
                <div>
                    <head>Chunks</head>
                    <p>In a prose text, the division will be made up of paragraphs, or other blocks, lists, etc. In a
                        poetic text, there will be verse lines, possibly grouped into stanzas. In a dramatic text, there
                        will be speeches, each containing a speaker identifiers and either a paragraph or some verse.
                        The following elements are used to encode these components: <specList>
                            <specDesc key="p"/>
                            <specDesc key="ab"/>
                            <specDesc key="list"/>
                            <specDesc key="item"/>
                            <specDesc key="label"/>
                            <specDesc key="lg"/>
                            <specDesc key="l"/>
                            <specDesc key="sp"/>
                            <specDesc key="speaker"/>
                        </specList></p>
                    <p>Notes and stage directions are represented using the following elements: <specList>
                            <specDesc key="stage"/>
                            <specDesc key="note"/>
                        </specList></p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <head>Phrase level components</head>
                    <p>The following elements are used to indicate commonly distinguished types of phrase : <specList>
                            <specDesc key="hi"/>
                            <specDesc key="q"/>
                            <specDesc key="foreign"/>
                            <specDesc key="date"/>
                            <specDesc key="title"/>
                            <specDesc key="name"/>
                        </specList></p>
                    <p>The generic <gi>seg</gi> is available to mark any other word or phrase to be distinguished for any other reason:
                    <specList>
                        <specDesc key="seg" atts="type subtype"/>
                    </specList>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <head>Milestones and pointers</head>
                    <p>The following elements are used to indicate significant milestones occurring throughout the text <specList>
                            <specDesc key="milestone"/>
                            <specDesc key="cb"/>
                            <specDesc key="lb"/>
                            <specDesc key="pb"/>
                        </specList></p>
                    <p>The following element is used to represent a cross reference of any kind: <specList>
                            <specDesc key="ref"/>
                        </specList>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <head>Editorial interventions</head>
                    <p>The following elements are used to indicate variation in the transcription.<specList>
                            <specDesc key="add"/>
                            <specDesc key="del"/>
                            <specDesc key="corr"/>
                            <specDesc key="sic"/>
                            <specDesc key="reg"/>
                            <specDesc key="orig"/>
                            <specDesc key="choice"/>
                        </specList></p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <head>Non-textual components</head>
                    <p>The following elements are used for non-textual components such as graphics, tables, music, or
                        formulae: <specList>
                            <specDesc key="figure"/>
                            <specDesc key="graphic"/>
                            <specDesc key="figDesc"/>
                            <specDesc key="formula"/>
                            <specDesc key="notatedMusic"/>
                            <specDesc key="row"/>
                            <specDesc key="table"/>
                            <specDesc key="cell"/>
                        </specList>
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div>
                    <head>Bibliographic elements</head>
                    <p>The following specialist elements are used for marking up the internal structure of bibliographic
                        descriptions <specList>
                            <specDesc key="author"/>
                            <specDesc key="bibl"/>
                            <specDesc key="biblScope"/>
                            <specDesc key="editor"/>
                            <specDesc key="imprint"/>
                            <specDesc key="pubPlace"/>
                            <specDesc key="publisher"/>
                            <specDesc key="resp"/>
                            <specDesc key="respStmt"/>
                            <specDesc key="series"/>
                            <specDesc key="listBibl"/>
                        </specList></p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div>
                <head>Metadata</head>
                
                <p><specList><specDesc key="availability"/>
                    <specDesc key="change"/>
                    <specDesc key="creation"/>
                    <specDesc key="edition"/>
                    <specDesc key="editionStmt"/>
                    <specDesc key="editorialDecl"/>
                    <specDesc key="encodingDesc"/>
                    <specDesc key="extent"/>
                    <specDesc key="fileDesc"/>
                    <specDesc key="funder"/>
                    <specDesc key="idno"/>
                    <specDesc key="langUsage"/>
                    <specDesc key="language"/>
                    <specDesc key="licence"/>
                    <specDesc key="listChange"/>
                    <specDesc key="listPrefixDef"/>
                    <specDesc key="notesStmt"/>
                    <specDesc key="prefixDef"/>
                    <specDesc key="profileDesc"/>
                    <specDesc key="projectDesc"/>
                    <specDesc key="publicationStmt"/>
                    <specDesc key="revisionDesc"/>
                    <specDesc key="sourceDesc"/>
                    <specDesc key="textClass"/>
                    <specDesc key="titleStmt"/></specList></p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <head>Facsimiles</head>
                <p>
                    <specList>
                        <specDesc key="surfaceGrp"/>
                        <specDesc key="surface"/>
                        <specDesc key="zone"/>
                        <specDesc key="line"/>
                    </specList></p>
            </div>
            <div>
                <head>Formal definitions</head>
                <schemaSpec ident="tei" docLang="fr" prefix="tei_" start="TEI" xml:lang="en" targetLang="en">
                    <moduleRef key="core"
                        include="add choice corr del author bibl biblScope cb date
                    editor foreign graphic head  hi imprint  item l label 
                    lb lg list listBibl milestone name note orig p pb  pubPlace publisher q 
                    ref reg resp respStmt series sp speaker stage title"/>
                    <moduleRef key="tei"/>
                    <moduleRef key="header"
                        include="availability change creation edition 
                    editionStmt editorialDecl encodingDesc extent
                    fileDesc funder idno langUsage language licence 
                    listChange listPrefixDef notesStmt prefixDef
                    profileDesc projectDesc publicationStmt
                    revisionDesc sourceDesc teiHeader textClass titleStmt"/>
                    
                    <moduleRef key="textstructure"
                        include="TEI back body byline dateline div docAuthor docDate docEdition 
                    docImprint docTitle epigraph front imprimatur text titlePage titlePart opener closer signed salute"/>
                    <moduleRef key="figures" include="cell figDesc figure formula notatedMusic row table"/>
                    <moduleRef key="linking" include="ab seg"/>
                   
                    <moduleRef key="transcr" include="facsimile line surfaceGrp surface zone"/>
                    
                    <elementSpec ident="div" mode="change" module="textstructure">
                        <attList>
                            <attDef ident="type" mode="change">
                                <valList mode="replace" type="semi">
                                    <valItem ident="source">
                                        <desc>material from a source</desc>
                                    </valItem>
                                    <valItem ident="note">
                                        <desc>annotations</desc>
                                    </valItem>
                                    <valItem ident="preface">
                                        <desc>prefatory comments</desc>
                                    </valItem>
                                    <valItem ident="other">
                                        <desc>autre</desc>
                                    </valItem>
                                </valList>
                            </attDef>
                        </attList>
                    </elementSpec>
                    
                    <classSpec ident="att.global" mode="change" type="atts" module="tei">
                        <attList>
                            <attDef ident="rendition" mode="delete"/>
                            <attDef ident="xml:base" mode="delete"/>
                            <attDef ident="pstyle" mode="add" ns="http://ns.adobe.com/AdobeInDesign/4.0/">
                                <desc> Correspondance de mise en forme dans Indesign (à l'échelle du paragraphe).</desc>
                                <datatype><rng:text/></datatype>
                            </attDef>
                            <attDef ident="cstyle" mode="add" ns="http://ns.adobe.com/AdobeInDesign/4.0/">
                                <desc> Correspondance de mise en forme dans Indesign (à l'échelle de la séquence de
                                    caractères).</desc>
                                <datatype><rng:text/></datatype>
                            </attDef>
                        </attList>
                    </classSpec>
                    
